<headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 14 at 9:51PM CDT  by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern
Pushmataha and south central Pittsburg Counties through 1015 PM
CDT...
At 951 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm 7 miles
southeast of Kiowa, moving east at 10 mph.
HAZARD...Penny size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.
Locations in or near the path include...
Kiowa...                          Pittsburg...
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.75 IN
MAX WIND GUST...&lt;30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
